Hope you don't mind me posting. I have a really nice casting call I‚Äôm working on :)

Please share with anyone who might like to apply.  

This is a fully paid project for anyone successful :) 

Applicants need to apply asap by today!

Children: ¬£200 day fee with a ¬£1500 buyout if featured in final commercial 

Email: [streetcasting@kharmelcochrane.co.uk](mailto:streetcasting@kharmelcochrane.co.uk) with a picture, full names, ages, location and a little about yourself.

[https://kharmelcochrane.com/](https://kharmelcochrane.com/)

Many Thanks

Lauren

Familiar Faces Casting Call Short Fim Directed by: Daniela Aguirre DATE POSTED: 09-22-2025 POSSIBLE SHOOTING DATES: November 8th OR November 9th, 2025 Rehearsal dates: TBD Location: Chicago, IL
We are committed to diverse, inclusive casting. For every role, please submit qualifiec performers, without regard to disability, race, age, color, national origin, ethnic origin, sexua orientation, gender identity, or any other basis prohibited by law unless otherwise specifically indicated.
Logline : A college undergrad soaring to become a pediatric speech therapist is taunted by ar unexplainable nightmare that has gradually become worse over time.
Roles:
Katalina Desdemona (22) ( Portrayed female Lead) - A senior year college undergrad who grew up in an abusive houschold that impacted her by severely delaying her speech development. With ome help from her ELD teacher (English Language Development) Katalina was able to express herself more growing up and dreams of doing the same for others,
Young Katalina (7-9) (Portrayed female- lead)- Evil spirit who imitates the appearance o Katalina when she was younger. Who's seeking to collect her promised teeth.
Pierre Baker (22) (Portrayed male- supporting)- The loyal best friend of Katalina since 5" grade and who also took interest in studying for child development and literacy. Dedicated and nurturing best friend
If interested, available, or have questions email Daniela Aguirre Send headshots, resumes/reels 

to email: daguirre2@colum.edu

Deadline Date: October 24th. 2025
Compensation: Meal, Copy, Credit

GWC is seeking people to portray 1960s White Upscale Gala Attendees (Ages 30-99) for upcoming A24 horror series MAMAS BOY

To submit, email mamasboy@gwcnyc.com with all the following info using the subject line
‚ÄúIG Gala‚Äù

Full name

Are you a SAG-AFTRA member in good standing (include SAG number) or non-SAG

Phone number

Are you fully available for shoot on 10/9, 10/10 & a TBD fitting?

Please note current height, weight, clothing and shoe sizes*

Please note if you have any tattoos or piercings, and attach a photo

Are you comfortable around atmospheric smoke?

If 21+, are you comfortable smoking a herbal cigarette, if asked? (It‚Äôs ok if not)

Men: Are you comfortable being clean shaven for the shoot if needed?

Men & women: Are you comfortable receiving a 1960‚Äôs haircut on set, if needed?

Are you local to NJ/NY area?

Confirm you are 18 years or older

Attach current, clear photos (close-up and full body)

This background role is not covered by SAG-AFTRA CBA and subject to a preference of employment provision.

*Height, weight, and clothing sizes are used for costuming purposes only, unless needed for the casting of stand-ins or photodoubles.
Please note, you must be able to present valid identification to fill out a federal I-9 form and be paid.

Hello, Nice to meet you. 

I'm Yoshikazu Saito, a Tokyo-based actor currently producing a film. And for this project, I'd like to show the story of a man born in japan and adopted in United States. It is Japanese cinema but, to challenge norms, in Japanglish. I mean in Japanese-English.

Currently, we need more financial support to develop the film. With your donate of our film, we could continue with our concept, showing that we have our ways of owning universal languages.

Below is a link to our PayPal, open for your support for our vision. And please share the proposal with your friends. 

Our team will also appreciate if you will share it with your friends as well.

Thank you very much and I wish you have a great day.
 

Donate via PayPal.Me
https://paypal.me/tvt2010?locale.x=ja_JP&country.x=JP
 
 
Proposal of Feature Film "An Adoptee -I am American-"
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ozp8wwbznVDmK_EAX0XXLIoEn153lvdl/view?usp=drivesdk

 
Producer Yoshikazu Saito
IMDb  https://www.imdb.com/name/nm14690380/?ef_fn_al_nm_1
 
Website    https://entertainment.tvt.co.jp/pages/6707910/page_202301050853
 
X  @yoshi7777888    https://twitter.com/yoshi777888?lang=ja
 
Instagram   @yoshi777888   https://www.instagram.com/yoshi777888/

**CASTING CALL - Concert Attendees for *****SHOTGUN***

We‚Äôre looking for enthusiastic people to be part of the audience in our upcoming project ***SHOTGUN*** - a new film currently in production.

**Details:**
* **Role:** Concert Attendees (background)

* **Date:** **Saturday, 4th September**

* **Commitment:** 1 full day

* **Location:** TBC (in Auckland - details provided upon confirmation)

* **Payment:** This is an unpaid role.

This is a volunteer opportunity, but a great chance to experience being on set, collaborate with a passionate team, and bring a live concert scene to life on screen. We‚Äôd also love to keep you in mind for future projects with us.

**What we‚Äôre looking for:**
* Energetic, expressive people

* No acting experience needed - just enthusiasm and commitment for the day

**How to apply:**
 If you‚Äôre keen, please email us at [lazybonesfilms@gmail.com](mailto:lazybonesfilms@gmail.com) with your:
* Name and contact details

* A recent photo (so we know who‚Äôs who on the day)

For more details about ‚ÄòSHOTGUN‚Äô: [https://www.thearts.co.nz/boosted/projects/shotgun](https://www.thearts.co.nz/boosted/projects/shotgun) 

We can‚Äôt wait to have you join us for this shoot and to make something special together.
* *Lazy Bones Films*

**COVER DRAMA TEACHER NEEDED TODAY 25/9 - ¬£35 per hour - Clapton area E5**

 

Good day, everyone!

 

Here at Dance&Arts, we are currently looking for a lovely teacher to cover our available Drama Afterschool Club TODAY Thursday, 25th September.

 

Please see the details below:

 

‚Ä¢  Cover Drama Afterschool Club

‚Ä¢  TODAY Thursday, 25th September | 4:00 - 5:00 PM

‚Ä¢  In a primary school in the Clapton area, E5

‚Ä¢  Kids are from KS1 (6-7 years old)

 

üëâ Pay is ¬£35 per hour.

 

‚ö† ESSENTIAL: Enhanced DBS check, commitment, and high reliability. ‚ö†

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

ùêìùê´ùêöùêßùê¨ùêüùê®ùê´ùê¶ ùêòùê®ùêÆùê´ùê¨ùêûùê•ùêü ùêàùêßùê≠ùê® ùêçùê®ùê≠ ùêâùêÆùê¨ùê≠ ùêö ùêèùê´ùê®ùêüùêûùê¨ùê¨ùê¢ùê®ùêßùêöùê• ùêÄùêúùê≠ùê®ùê´, ùêÅùêÆùê≠ ùêöùêß ùêîùêßùê¨ùê≠ùê®ùê©ùê©ùêöùêõùê•ùêû ùêÖùê®ùê´ùêúùêû ùê∞ùê¢ùê≠ùê° ùêåùêöùê´ùêõùê•ùêû ùêÄùêúùêöùêùùêûùê¶ùê≤!

** **

Whether you're just starting or want to improve the talent you already have, Marble Academy in Swinton, Manchester, will help unlock your full potential and refine your craft to help capture the attention of casting directors in film, television, and theatre.

 

Here‚Äôs why you should seize this incredible opportunity:

**Renowned Excellence**: Marble Academy is not only celebrated by Spotlight as one of the premier drama academies in the country, but is also the recipient of the ùêåùêöùêßùêúùê°ùêûùê¨ùê≠ùêûùê´ & ùêçùê®ùê´ùê≠ùê° ùêñùêûùê¨ùê≠ ùêèùê´ùêûùê¨ùê≠ùê¢ùê†ùêû ùêÄùê∞ùêöùê´ùêùùê¨ ùêüùê®ùê´ ùêìùê°ùêûùêöùê≠ùê´ùêû ùêíùêúùê°ùê®ùê®ùê• ùêéùêü ùêìùê°ùêû ùêòùêûùêöùê´.
Here, you won‚Äôt just learn; you‚Äôll train with one of the best in the business!

 

**Authentic Training**: Our L.A.M.D.A.-qualified tutor, Christian Le Feuvre, brings a wealth of real-world experience that empowers you to delve deeply into characters and scenes. His insightful feedback doesn‚Äôt just boost your confidence; it ignites your growth as an actor, providing you with a fresh perspective on every script. With his nurturing and constructive coaching style, you‚Äôll be amazed at how he can transform your journey as an actor.

 

But don‚Äôt just take our word for it‚Äîexplore the glowing reviews and dive into our programme details for a closer look at what we offer at www.marbleacademy.co.uk

 

Audition dates are still available!

 

Don‚Äôt let this incredible opportunity pass you by‚Äîtake the first step towards a world of extraordinary possibilities in your acting career‚Äîemail [marbleacademy@hotmail.com](mailto:marbleacademy@hotmail.com) for more information and to book your audition slot.

,,..... schlie√üen Sie vorsichtshalber eine Insassenversicherung ab, Gute Reise"
 Ein ehemaligerBND-Mitar-
beiter kehrt nach Jahren in seine Heimat zur√ºck. 
Dort, in den Ammergauer Alpen, liegt die ber√ºchtigte Messerschmitt-H√∂hle, ein Ort seiner Kindheit, um den sich schon immer Ger√ºchte rankten. Was einst f√ºr ihn nur  Abenteuerfantasie war, entpuppt sich nun als d√ºstere Realit√§t: eine ehemalige U-Verlagerung, in der w√§hrend des Zweiten Weltkriegs kriegswichtige R√ºstungsprojekte im Verborgenen betrieben wurden.
 Als er zuf√§llig auf alte Akten und unvollst√§ndige Baupl√§ne st√∂√üt, wird aus Neugier eine lebensgef√§hrliche Recherche. 
  Denn die H√∂hle ist nicht nur ein Relikt der Vergangenheit ‚Äì sie ist bis heute Teil eines Netzes geheimer Infrastrukturen, das √ºber Deutschland und √ñsterreich hinaus bis nach Moldawien reicht. Die unterirdischen Korridore, einst mit Tarnnamen verschleiert, f√ºhren weiter, als es irgendjemand f√ºr m√∂glich hielt ‚Äì bis nach Moskau.
 Pl√∂tzlich steht er im Fadenkreuz jener Kr√§fte, die seit Jahrzehnten alles daransetzen, diese Verbindung geheim zu halten. Doch wer die Wahrheit ans Licht bringt, bringt auch ein Machtgef√ºge ins Wanken, das Europa bis in seine Grundfesten ersch√ºttern k√∂nnte.

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

items.text:
**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss‚Äôs unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5‚Äô2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she‚Äôs having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a ‚Äúnoncompetitive and ineffectual environment‚Äù would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she‚Äôs found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She‚Äôs annoyed she was moved onto Hannah‚Äôs task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She‚Äôs not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin‚Äô Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a ‚ÄúGreybeard‚Äù or municipal government. He‚Äôs been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He‚Äôs incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a ‚Äúhealthy dose‚Äù of political corruption. He likes ambitious people that know what they want, and won‚Äôt let moral or legal guidelines stifle their vision. He saw a lot of potential in Hannah when she started as his assistant. When Hannah hit her rock bottom, it was his idea to give her a leave of absence, as he felt a sense of responsibility for her. He‚Äôs given Hannah six months to show what she‚Äôs made of. If it works, he looks like a genius. If she fails, it‚Äôs not much money, his conscience is clear and in the meantime he can use the Task Force to his own personal and financial benefit when the opportunity arises.

***CHARACTER****:  *Nick

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***28

***Episode: ****2*

***Appearance: ***White, thin and kind of scrawny. Slim shady like. Oshawa generals jersey. Knock off designer hat and shoes. Chain. Energetic, passionate, feels his emotions and is confident in them, which can make him a prima donna. The fashion of J Roc, the delivery of Western U frat bro, and the sincerity of a ‚Äúcool‚Äù youth pastor, 

***About Character:**** *After getting his Bachelors from Western, Nick gave up on higher education to pursue his dream of becoming a hip hop legend. He moved back in with his mom and  new husband, Bill Tuft, at his mansion. That was 5 years ago. When Bill learns that the Task Force is putting together a tourism music video, he sees this as an opportunity to include Nick in order to write off past studio personal expenses. Nick joins forces with Jam Easy in making a great song, and wins his step-dad‚Äôs respect of his art. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Gord ‚ÄúConspiracy Guy‚Äù 

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***39

***Episode: ****2,4*

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who‚Äôs stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his ‚Äúauditing‚Äù police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He‚Äôs paranoid, he‚Äôs ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he‚Äôs very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for ‚Äúinvading his privacy‚Äù and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ‚Äùspy drone‚Äù, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù life wasn‚Äôt wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - ‚ÄúOshawa‚Äù, but is legally required to let the task force know he‚Äôs not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he‚Äôs the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah‚Äôs communication with her team.

***CHARACTER****:  *Willie

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***66

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thinning white/grey uncombed hair, beer belly, red face, weathered skin. Slow moving and a slow vocal pace. He never wants to finish his sentence because it‚Äôll give the listener a chance to leave. Vintage, worn rumpled clothes. A hat that looks like he‚Äôs been wearing it for 50 years. 

***About Character:**** *A local Oshawa ‚ÄúShwallywood legend‚Äù that has had hundreds of TV and Movie productions use his driveway. A lonely drinker and compulsive liar, a bad one at that, When Jam Easy needs to stall on his Hollywood Tour, he brings his group to Willie, who shares ‚ÄúForrest Gumpian‚Äù stories of how he changed movie history, and bragging about absurdly close friendships with movie stars. Obviously no one believes him, which makes him sad. He just just excited to have someone to talk to.

***CHARACTER****:*  Clara ‚ÄúNewswoman‚Äù

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***40‚Äôs

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Mid-40s, attractive but not delicate, with a confident, professional presence. Simple hair, and a face showing experience rather than youth. Blazer, smart blouse, tailored slacks. Carries a small microphone with the channel logo, Minimal jewelry. 

***About Character: ***Field reporter for a Durham Region news channel. Polished but practical, someone who can run to a chaotic scene without ruining her outfit. Clara is on-site at the Oshawa tourism task force‚Äôs Hollywood Tour location, where a body has been discovered. She delivers the story with gravity despite the absurdity of the situation. 

***CHARACTER****:* Chris

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Medium build, white, dark hair. Nerdy, glasses, thrifted clothes or ones he picked up at Costco

***About Character: ***full-time software engineer but would rather talk about his many hobbies and interests like the golden age of cinema, Napoleon, his tropical fish tank, pickleball league and making his girlfriend Julia happy. Chris saw an online ad for the Shwallywood Tour and immediately booked it as he had been looking for a way to propose to his girlfriend, Julia, for months. On the day of, Chris does not immediately react when the tour seems to be taking much longer than anticipated to get to Parkwood as he is a calm and patient person. He only becomes upset when he sees his girlfriend Julia is disappointed in the lackluster activities of the day.

***CHARACTER****:*  Julia

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thin frame, blonde or dark brown hair, A little nerdy, soft goth. 

***About Character: ***Works as a dental assistant. She realized she had a passion for teeth when she did a work placement as a mortician in high school. Julia has been taken on the Shwallywood tour by Chris, to celebrate their anniversary. She initially had very little interest, but Chris insisted on bringing her because she‚Äôs a movie buff. The tour is off to a rough start, but as the tour progresses, Julia‚Äôs eccentric side emerges. She enjoys the macabre and is intrigued by some of the stranger stops, though her frustration continues as Chris struggles to give an honest take on the experience.

items.summary:
**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss‚Äôs unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5‚Äô2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she‚Äôs having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a ‚Äúnoncompetitive and ineffectual environment‚Äù would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she‚Äôs found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She‚Äôs annoyed she was moved onto Hannah‚Äôs task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She‚Äôs not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin‚Äô Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a ‚ÄúGreybeard‚Äù or municipal government. He‚Äôs been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He‚Äôs incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a ‚Äúhealthy dose‚Äù of political corruption. He likes ambitious people that know what they want, and won‚Äôt let moral or legal guidelines stifle their vision. He saw a lot of potential in Hannah when she started as his assistant. When Hannah hit her rock bottom, it was his idea to give her a leave of absence, as he felt a sense of responsibility for her. He‚Äôs given Hannah six months to show what she‚Äôs made of. If it works, he looks like a genius. If she fails, it‚Äôs not much money, his conscience is clear and in the meantime he can use the Task Force to his own personal and financial benefit when the opportunity arises.

***CHARACTER****:  *Nick

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***28

***Episode: ****2*

***Appearance: ***White, thin and kind of scrawny. Slim shady like. Oshawa generals jersey. Knock off designer hat and shoes. Chain. Energetic, passionate, feels his emotions and is confident in them, which can make him a prima donna. The fashion of J Roc, the delivery of Western U frat bro, and the sincerity of a ‚Äúcool‚Äù youth pastor, 

***About Character:**** *After getting his Bachelors from Western, Nick gave up on higher education to pursue his dream of becoming a hip hop legend. He moved back in with his mom and  new husband, Bill Tuft, at his mansion. That was 5 years ago. When Bill learns that the Task Force is putting together a tourism music video, he sees this as an opportunity to include Nick in order to write off past studio personal expenses. Nick joins forces with Jam Easy in making a great song, and wins his step-dad‚Äôs respect of his art. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Gord ‚ÄúConspiracy Guy‚Äù 

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***39

***Episode: ****2,4*

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who‚Äôs stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his ‚Äúauditing‚Äù police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He‚Äôs paranoid, he‚Äôs ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he‚Äôs very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for ‚Äúinvading his privacy‚Äù and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ‚Äùspy drone‚Äù, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù life wasn‚Äôt wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - ‚ÄúOshawa‚Äù, but is legally required to let the task force know he‚Äôs not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he‚Äôs the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah‚Äôs communication with her team.

***CHARACTER****:  *Willie

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***66

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thinning white/grey uncombed hair, beer belly, red face, weathered skin. Slow moving and a slow vocal pace. He never wants to finish his sentence because it‚Äôll give the listener a chance to leave. Vintage, worn rumpled clothes. A hat that looks like he‚Äôs been wearing it for 50 years. 

***About Character:**** *A local Oshawa ‚ÄúShwallywood legend‚Äù that has had hundreds of TV and Movie productions use his driveway. A lonely drinker and compulsive liar, a bad one at that, When Jam Easy needs to stall on his Hollywood Tour, he brings his group to Willie, who shares ‚ÄúForrest Gumpian‚Äù stories of how he changed movie history, and bragging about absurdly close friendships with movie stars. Obviously no one believes him, which makes him sad. He just just excited to have someone to talk to.

***CHARACTER****:*  Clara ‚ÄúNewswoman‚Äù

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***40‚Äôs

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Mid-40s, attractive but not delicate, with a confident, professional presence. Simple hair, and a face showing experience rather than youth. Blazer, smart blouse, tailored slacks. Carries a small microphone with the channel logo, Minimal jewelry. 

***About Character: ***Field reporter for a Durham Region news channel. Polished but practical, someone who can run to a chaotic scene without ruining her outfit. Clara is on-site at the Oshawa tourism task force‚Äôs Hollywood Tour location, where a body has been discovered. She delivers the story with gravity despite the absurdity of the situation. 

***CHARACTER****:* Chris

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Medium build, white, dark hair. Nerdy, glasses, thrifted clothes or ones he picked up at Costco

***About Character: ***full-time software engineer but would rather talk about his many hobbies and interests like the golden age of cinema, Napoleon, his tropical fish tank, pickleball league and making his girlfriend Julia happy. Chris saw an online ad for the Shwallywood Tour and immediately booked it as he had been looking for a way to propose to his girlfriend, Julia, for months. On the day of, Chris does not immediately react when the tour seems to be taking much longer than anticipated to get to Parkwood as he is a calm and patient person. He only becomes upset when he sees his girlfriend Julia is disappointed in the lackluster activities of the day.

***CHARACTER****:*  Julia

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thin frame, blonde or dark brown hair, A little nerdy, soft goth. 

***About Character: ***Works as a dental assistant. She realized she had a passion for teeth when she did a work placement as a mortician in high school. Julia has been taken on the Shwallywood tour by Chris, to celebrate their anniversary. She initially had very little interest, but Chris insisted on bringing her because she‚Äôs a movie buff. The tour is off to a rough start, but as the tour progresses, Julia‚Äôs eccentric side emerges. She enjoys the macabre and is intrigued by some of the stranger stops, though her frustration continues as Chris struggles to give an honest take on the experience.

items.text:
Hello folks, my Film And Video Production students decided to begin a very ambitious project - Feature Film! Those of you who work in the industry already know how much time, effort and money it take to do a good movie, for those of you who don't know I can tell you - a lot! If you like to help them on their journey, please take a time to read their message below and if you decide to help them, please follow the link to their GoFundMe page. I've seen them in action and I've read the script, this project worth to be filmed!                                                                                                                                         

What happens when film students try to wrangle Greek Gods on a student budget?

Hey Calgary film fam, 

We're a group of SAIT film students in our final semester, and we've taken on our biggest project yet : Prometheion - a student-led feature film inspired by Greek mythology, with a bonus BTS to show the beautiful chaos making it. 

We're pouring in long day and nights, all our are creativity, and yes... way too much craft table pizza. But to really bring this story to life, we could use some extra support for wardrobe, props, locations, and keeping our crew alive through it all. 

Here's our GoFundMe : https://www.gofundme.com/f/prometheion-student-feature-film?attribution_id=sl:0597d4f7-f1e5-4ff2-86ce-2da6a9373dd2&lang=en_CA&ts=1758595706 

 Every bit helps us make this film with the ambition it deserves, and we'd be so grateful if you can contribute or share. 

 Thanks for helping us light the fire of Prometheion!

items.text: Hi guys, why don't we make our own films? Like let's gather around and start talking to know each other. I'm sure everyone has some equipment, it could be anything. What do you think?

items.text:
Actors Wisdom for Wednesdays!

A reminder for all of us: courage in performance, and in life, often means speaking up, even when it feels hardest.

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Speak your mind, even if your voice shakes. Maggie Smith'

items.text:
Hi,

sharedPost.text:
Alternate Shadows continued their Murder Mystery run on 

Sat night in Boughton Mochelsea, Maidstone for the Trefoil Guild. 

The Guild allows members to give back and give support. Whether this is to the community or causes important to the individual, supporting friends and members, or finding support for oneself.

We shall be next appearing at the Three Daws Pub, Gravesend on 

Saturday 4th October for The Gravesend, Northfleet & District u3a.

The Three Daws is an Historic pub dating back to the 1400's and steeped with tales of smugglers, Press Gangs, hauntings and much more.

items.text:
Hey everyone my name is Manraj Heer I‚Äôm the producer for our student short film at Vancouver Film School. The film is called ‚ÄúBeginnings‚Äù and we are shooting on October 11th & 12th, 2025. We are currently looking to hire three male actors. For the roles of Athan, Hooded Man, and Rick. If you are interested please send your resume, headshot, and any demo reel to teambeginnings@gmail.com and we will reach out to you for a self tape to help narrow down the process.

The deadline for demo tapes and applications end on October 3rd, 2025. So please get in your application at your earliest convenience.

Synopsis:
Athan celebrates his 21st birthday surrounded by the people he loves the most. Family and
friends cheer for the start of a new phase of Athan‚Äôs life. A new beginning. Until time suddenly
stops. Everyone freezing in place, except for Athan, who knows the memory has ended.
Guided by a Hooded Man, an older and wiser version of himself, Athan must find purpose by
visiting rooms in a seemingly never-ending hallway, each filled with crucial moments of his life
‚Äî learning the role of the people that surround him (and the impact he has on them), dealing
with love in an ever-transforming relationship, and embracing grief from the never-stopping
passage of time.
After impulsively deciding to skip entering the rest of the doors out of agony, Athan will find
how quickly a lifetime goes by ‚Äî but be ready to accept his new chapter behind a final, bright room.

CASTING BREAKDOWN ‚Äì VANCOUVER FILM SCHOOL
Project Title: Beginnings
Project Type: Student Short Film
Union Status: Non-Union
Director: J. D. Estevez
Producer: Raj Heer / Vancouver Film School
Casting Director: Manraj Heer, J. D. Estevez
Audition Dates: Self-tapes due by October 3rd, 2025
Audition Location: Self-tapes only
Call Back Dates: October 4th, 2025
Call Back Location: 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2
Shooting Dates: October 11th ‚Äì 12th, 2025
Shooting Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Rates: Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.
Submission Instructions: Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel
to teambeginnings@gmail.com and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

ATHAN / MALE / AGE : 20-25 / ANY ETHNICITY 

Na√Øve and foolish, Athan thinks he knows what he wants from life and what it is to be expected of him ‚Äî learning soon enough that you can never be prepared for what is behind
the next door. Though he is slow to realize the importance of every moment, and too clumsy
to show it, Athan is a deeply caring and empathetic person. He is willing to push everything
out of his way to spend more time with someone he loves. Despite repeatedly stumbling
through the hallway of life, Athan is motivated by a constant search for meaning.

HOODED MAN / MALE / AGE : 50-60 / ANY ETHNICITY
After living as a rebellious young Athan, the Hooded Man walks through the hallway of his life
once again. This time, he reflects on his past, accepting it for what it is, knowing he cannot
change it. Melancholic and somewhat regretful, he guides Athan, emphasizing the
importance of embracing every stage of life, whether joyful or somber. Unlike his younger
self, the Hooded Man moves deliberately through every memory, without hurry, but with
peace. Though seemingly stoic, there is a hint of disturbance behind his expression.

RICK / MALE / AGE : 40-50 / ANY ETHNICITY
Athan‚Äôs father, Rick, is a troubled man. He learned from his family to hide his true feelings and
often relies on bad habits to forget his past mistakes. He was able to distance himself from his
vices when he found a sense of purpose, such as when he married his childhood friend,
Emma. However, it didn't last long. Overwhelmed by regret and fearing that he won‚Äôt make
the most of his life, Rick sees Athan as a chance to start over. He is determined to ensure that
his son won't make the same mistakes he did. However, with his marriage falling apart and
Athan soon becoming independent, Rick can‚Äôt help but start drinking again.

 Look forward to seeing everyone‚Äôs submissions! If you have any questions or concerns please reach me at teambeginnings@gmail.com.

üì£ Casting Call ‚Äì Vancouver üé¨
We‚Äôre filming a volunteer-based music video Not Close (non-union). Meals and credit provided.

‚ú® Andy (Lead, Female, 20‚Äì35) ‚Äì A young woman juggling work and life, quietly resilient yet vulnerable.
üóìÔ∏è Shoots: Oct 11 & 12

‚ú® The Kid (Supporting, any gender, 4‚Äì10) ‚Äì Sweet, energetic, and curious. The heart of the reunion.
üóìÔ∏è Shoots: Oct 12

‚ú® The Boss (Supporting, Male or Female, 30‚Äì60) ‚Äì Stern, short-tempered, represents the grind Andy is stuck in.
üóìÔ∏è Shoots: Oct 11

Synopsis:
Not Close tells the story of Andy, a young woman pushing through the daily grind, unanswered calls, and isolation ‚Äî until a heartfelt reunion with her child brings light back into her world.

üì© To submit: send headshot + resume (demo reel if available) to valerie.film.prod@gmail.com

items.text:
‚ÄúScrooge! (Abbreviated Version)‚Äù 

Book, Music and Lyrics by Leslie Bricusse

From A Christmas Carol by Charles Dickens

A one-hour adaptation of the crowd-pleasing holiday musical!

In 1970, renowned writer/composer/lyricist Leslie Bricusse adapted the classic Charles Dickens tale A Christmas Carol into the hit screen musical Scrooge! 

A charming stage musical, Scrooge! 

Lyons Community Theatre

Auditions: Will be held at Planet Bluegrass Lab Building(Directions), on Friday, Oct 3rd, 5-7pm; Sunday, Oct 5th,  1-3pm and Monday, Oct 6th, 5-7pm  (If none of these days or times work for you, please contact georgi.pollard@gmail.com by Sunday, Oct 5th @12pm

Performance dates:

Friday, December 12th, 2025 @7pm 

Saturday, December 13th, 2025 @2pm & 7pm

Sunday, December 14th, 2025 @2pm 

@Planet Bluegrass Wildflower Pavillion 

All auditioners  will be asked to sing 16 measures from the musical or a verse from a familiar holiday song.

We will dance a few moves and those wanting a speaking role will read from the script. Everyone is encouraged to show off your English accent!  Although not necessary, you are welcome to bring a prepared song to share.  We will have an accompanist.

Roles are Non-Union | Unpaid

LCT encourages actors of all races, ethnicities, genders, ages, and abilities all ages to audition, welcoming performers from all backgrounds.

Performers may come on any one of the days or you may sign up using the Signup Genius link

Link to Sign up for an Audition Slot:

SIGN UP LINK

https://www.signupgenius.com/go/70A0A4BA4A723ABFE3-58313489-scrooge#/

items.text:
Title: With the Skin

Genre: Psychological thriller

Logline: An infantilized woman sheltered by her overprotective mother is drawn to the outside world by a budding attraction to her charismatic neighbor. She must choose between the safety of the life she knew and the allure of the unknown.

Roles: 

**Ines** (female, 20s) *An infantilized woman beginning to venture from her protected bubble.*

**Evelyn** (female, 40s) *An overprotective mother, desperately trying to maintain her daughter‚Äôs innocence.*

**Wendy** (female, 20s) *A nosy drifter who moves in next door, always looking for excitement.*

**Johnny** (male, early 30s) *A pushy musician who lives to party.*

Production Type: CU Denver Junior Thesis student film

Contact Information: sarojadmanickam@gmail.com, sign up for in-person auditions or submit self tapes at [https://forms.gle/12DzeBY1Q7hK21St6](https://forms.gle/12DzeBY1Q7hK21St6)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: 

Evelyn $125/day

Ines $100/day

Wendy and Johnny will be unpaid

Food and transportation will be provided for all roles 

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: There will be in-person auditions at the Auraria Campus Library on October 2nd and October 3rd. Time slots are available on the QR code questionnaire.

Shooting Schedule: November 7th-9th (subject to slight changes) & a table read in mid-October

Filming Location: Primarily Castle Rock, CO - transportation can be arranged and provided

Project Description: This film contains sensitive material and depictions of sexual assault, cannibalism, and both emotional and physical abuse. These will be emotionally demanding roles, so make sure that you are comfortable and able to commit.

**$500 Finders Fee: Have You Been Ghosted By Your Husband Or Wife? (Docu-Series Casting)**

An acclaimed television production company and a major cable network are actively searching for women and men whose spouse has suddenly and mysteriously vanished, without warning, without explanation, and with no way to contact them. If you are still *legally married* but don‚Äôt know *where *your spouse is, you don‚Äôt have a clear explanation or *‚Äúwhy‚Äù* they left, or *how* to reach them, *we want to hear your story for a bold and empowering new series.*

**$500 Referral Fee: **Do You Know Someone? Share their information with us or simply have them tell us you referred them! Finders fee is paid IF referral is selected for production. 

*Selected for series candidates are compensated for taking part as well as receive expert help in tracking down their missing spouse, rebuilding their lives and finding closure. *

**To apply, please email: ****[casting@bodegapictures.com](mailto:casting@bodegapictures.com)****, **or visit: https://abandonedspouseshortapp.castingcrane.com/
